Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (175 degrees C). Blend together the cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and vanilla. Gently stir in pineapple, pour into pie crust. Sprinkle pecans over cream cheese mixture. Blend together the 3 eggs, corn syrup, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla. Pour over pecan layer. Place on lower rack of oven and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until center is firm.